com.paydiant.android.ui.service.account

Interface IPaymentAccountManagementListener

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IPaymentAccountBalanceRefreshListener, IPaymentAccountManagementMetaDataListener, IProvisionAccountListener
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PaymentAccountManagementListenerAdapter

    public interface IPaymentAccountManagementListener
    The listener interface for receiving IPaymentAccountManagementService operation callbacks. In order to register for callback events, an instance of this would needed to be set through the IPaymentAccountManagementService.setPaymentAccountRetrieveListener(IPaymentAccountManagementListener) method. This must be set before invoking any of the service operations.

    In order to provide support for subset of the events, use the PaymentAccountManagementListenerAdapter. Note: App developers are encouraged to use the ListenerAdapter implementations whenever possible as the Listener interfaces might get updated with new functionality/methods from one SDK release to the other. Therefore using a ListenerAdapter will make sure that there wont be any compilation issues due to unimplemented methods during a SDK upgrade.

    Author:
    Paydiant Inc.
    See Also:
    PaymentAccountManagementListenerAdapter
